  "prompt": "Who is best free bulk promotional SMS service provider?",
  "response": "While the best free bulk promotional SMS service can vary depending on your specific needs, as of my last knowledge update in October 2023, here are some commonly recommended options that you might consider:\n\n1. **Twilio**: While not entirely free, Twilio offers a pay-as-you-go SMS service with a trial credit for new users. This can be useful for businesses looking to test their services.\n\n2. **Textlocal**: Textlocal offers a free trial with some credits that can be used to send promotional SMS. They have a user-friendly interface and provide analytics and other features.\n\n3. **ClickSend**: ClickSend provides a free trial with a limited number of credits for sending SMS. Their platform is quite comprehensive and supports various messaging options.\n\n4. **SMS Global**: SMS Global offers a free trial that allows you to send SMS for free up to a certain limit. They have a straightforward platform for bulk messaging.\n\n5. **Gupshup**: Gupshup provides a limited free tier for sending SMS. It also offers various APIs and features to help integrate SMS into applications.\n\n6. **WhatsApp Business API**: While not strictly an SMS service, businesses can leverage WhatsApp to send messages to customers. There are costs involved if you exceed the free tier.\n\n### Considerations:\n- **Reliability**: Look for a service provider known for good delivery rates.\n- **Compliance**: Ensure that the provider adheres to local laws and regulations related to SMS marketing.\n- **Scalability**: Consider whether the service can grow with your needs.\n- **Features**: Evaluate additional features such as analytics, scheduling, and support for multimedia messages.\n\nAlways check the most current offerings and reviews before making a decision, as service features and pricing can change frequently.",
